    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nFrom a discussion on another issue, it seems like this was intentional, but I feel like it should be configurable at least.\n\nIf I for example have a very long filename, just saving that will result in the more window being opened. I would like to not turn off the message of it being saved, but I also don't want to be disrupted by the more window being opened. It feels like another `PRESS Enter to continue`\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5fec808a-286a-4214-8c18-41ff7dfe1dca\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ninit.lua\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._extui\").enable({ msg = { pos = \"box\" } })\n```\n\nCreate a file with a long filename, enable extui with pos = box, and save the file. The more window will open if it doesn't fit. This can happen quite a lot when I am using my laptop without an external screen, and for example have a split between my terminal and a browser\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the more window to not open\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-458+gcc264d51ab\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.34.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from source",
