            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think this should be configurable, because that means it _has_ to be configured. Instead, the goal is to have _semantic_ annotations for messages that allow them to be routed to the fitting outlet (instead of guessing based on output size). This means we need to distinguish\n1. explicit output (-> always to more window for inspection, searching, yanking)\n2. status messages as feedback to operations (success, error, warning, info -> routed to cmdarea or box, depending on `pos`)\n3. progress messages (-> routed to cmdarea or box, depending on `pos`, but in the latter case in a _fixed_ position_ so they overwrite; never added to `:messages`)\n\nIdeally, these message \"categories\" can be mapped from the existing message \"kinds\", although some heuristics may be necessary (for plugins with missing \"kinds\", for example). This would also centralize these routing decisions and make it easier to document and reason about them.",
