        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I can agree that it is not perfect to have it configurable, but it seems a bit weird to auto open the more window? I can read whatever is printed out in the box position, and if I see that some of it is truncated or doesn't fit, then I just open the window to read what I missed. Even if it is explicit output, it seems like we are trying to be smart to open the window for the user instead of just leaving that action for the user.\n\nWhat about having some sort of autocmd when messages come through, and then the user can just create an autocmd to open the more window automatically, instead of enforcing that\n\nIt really feels like a `PRESS enter to continue` prompt the way it is now",
